Recycled plastic lumber is gaining traction as a durable, low-maintenance material for outdoor decking, boardwalks, and park benches. Made from post-consumer plastic waste, this synthetic material resists rot, moisture, and insect damage, far outlasting traditional pressure-treated wood. By diverting plastic from landfills and oceans, its use supports circular economy principles while providing a splinter-free, weather-resistant solution for public infrastructure.
